goals.visualization: box plot of record and normal temperatures
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if record temperatures are significantly different from normal temperatures.

goals.question: What is the trend of actual temperatures over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of actual temperatures over time
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there is a pattern in the actual temperatures over time.

goals.question: What is the correlation between actual and forecast temperatures?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of actual and forecast temperatures
goals.rationale: This will help us understand if the forecasted temperatures are accurate.

goals.question: What is the distribution of actual temperatures?
goals.rationale: This will help us understand the range of actual temperatures and if there are any outliers.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data_to_plot = data[['record', 'normal']]
    sns.boxplot(data=data_to_plot)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of record temperatures compared to normal temperatures?", wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of actual temperatures over time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['difference'] = data['actual'] - data['normal']
    avg_difference = data['difference'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='day', y='difference', data=data)
    plt.axhline(avg_difference, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Difference: {avg_difference:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average difference between actual and normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
